==English==

===Etymology===
:from {{OF.}} ''participle'' (1388), "a noun-adjective", variant of ''[[participe]]'', from {{L.}} ''[[participium]]''

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|grammar}} a form of a verb that functions as an adjective and, when combined with a form of auxiliary verbs such as ''[[have]]'' or ''[[be]]'', forms certain [[tense]]s or [[mood]]s of the verb
#: ''I have '''loved''' you with an everlasting love.''
#: ''I am '''going''' to the store.''

====Usage notes====
In English, participles typically end in ''[[-ing]]'' or ''[[-ed]]''.

